<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id748bc0b9-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s90101"><num value="90101">§ 90101.</num><heading> Organization</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id748bc0ba-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s90101/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Federal Charter</inline>.—</heading><content>The Help America Vote Foundation (in this chapter, the “foundation”) is a federally chartered corporation.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id748bc0bb-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s90101/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Nature of Foundation</inline>.—</heading><content>The foundation is a charitable and nonprofit corporation and is not an agency or establishment of the United States Government.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id748bc0bc-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s90101/c"><num value="c">(c)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Perpetual Existence</inline>.—</heading><content>Except as otherwise provided, the foundation has perpetual existence.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id748bc0bd-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/107/252/tVI/s601/a">Pub. L. 107–252, title VI, § 601(a)</ref>, <date date="2002-10-29">Oct. 29, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1718">116 Stat. 1718</ref>, § 152601; renumbered § 90101, <ref href="/us/pl/113/237/s3/c/6/B">Pub. L. 113–237, § 3(c)(6)(B)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2840">128 Stat. 2840</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
